## Fair Use Examples

The following uses are allowed:
- Using OpenPact internally within your organisation
- Self-hosting OpenPact on your own servers
- Modifying the source code for internal use
- Offering consulting or support services related to OpenPact
  (e.g. building workflows, integrations, or custom agents for clients)
- Using OpenPact in academic or research settings
- Using OpenPact for personal projects

The following uses are NOT allowed without a separate commercial licence:
- Hosting OpenPact and charging users for access
- Embedding OpenPact in a paid product, service, or module where the
  value derives entirely or substantially from OpenPact functionality
- White-labelling OpenPact and offering it as your own product
- Offering a managed OpenPact service that competes with official
  OpenPact commercial offerings

If you are unsure whether your use is permitted, contact
license@openpact.dev.

